
[1]knife

   KNIFE,n. nife; plu. knives; nives.

   1. A cutting instrument with a sharp edge. Knives are of various shapes
   and sizes, adapted to their respective uses; as table knives; carving
   knives or carvers; penknives, &c.

   2. A sword or dagger.
